    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Camden</name>
                    <date when="1883-09-04" rend="right"><choice>
                            <abbr>Sept:</abbr>
                            <expan>September</expan>
                        </choice> 4 <choice>
                            <abbr>'83</abbr>
                            <expan>1883</expan>
                        </choice></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Harry</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>Yours of to-day with the 10 has safely <choice>
                    <abbr>reach'd</abbr>
                    <expan>reached</expan>
                </choice> me. Why have you sent it? It is singular &amp; unnecessary&#8212;<hi
                    rend="underline">you were entirely welcome, &amp; always have
                    been</hi><ptr target="med.00661_n1"/>&#8212;</p>

            <p>&#8212;I have been away most of the last five or six weeks at Germantown 9 or 10
                miles out[side] <choice>
                    <abbr>Phila.</abbr>
                    <expan>Philadelphia</expan>
                </choice> on a visit to very kind Quaker folks, particular friends of mine<ptr
                    target="med.00661_n2"/>&#8212;had a good time&#8212;good grub&#8212;a horse to
                my use to drive every day, (which I did, a long drive)&#8212;a large
                library&#8212;&amp;c. I am well as usual&#8212;nothing very new with my affairs (but
                the last six or eight months has kind of gone back on me)&#8212;I <choice>
                    <abbr>rec'd</abbr>
                    <expan>received</expan>
                </choice> a letter from Glendale<ptr target="med.00661_n3"/> from your
                mother <choice>
                    <abbr>ab't</abbr>
                    <expan>about</expan>
                </choice> three weeks ago&#8212;I have written two letters to her&#8212;</p>

            <p>&#8212;I don't know whether this will reach you as I am not certain of the right address&#8212;<choice><abbr>Havn't</abbr>
                    <expan>Haven't</expan>
                </choice> seen Mont<ptr target="med.00661_n4"/> for several weeks, but suppose he is
                here the same yet.</p>

            <closer>
                <signed rend="right">W W</signed>
                            </closer>
            <postscript>
                <p>Harry when you write tell me the exact way to address papers &amp;c. to you
                    through the PO</p>
            </postscript>
        </body>
        
